FBIS3-60862 "jptot001__l94110" JPRS-TOT-94-001-L Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Terrorism FOUO 7 January 1994 CENTRAL EURASIA RUSSIA Four Caucasians Kidnap Children; No Motive Given Hijackers Demand New Engine LD2612100793 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel Network in Russian 0858 GMT 26 Dec 93 LD2612100793 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel Network Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Unscheduled bulletin] [Excerpt] [passage omitted] The public relations center of the Russian Interior Ministry gives some details. At 0500 GMT the terrorists demanded vodka and a new helicopter since they think the engine of the one they are on is faulty. Contact with the criminals is still one-sided and is taking place on their initiative only. According to information at 0800 GMT, the helicopter is on a runway. There is no movement around it. The food demanded by the terrorists has been brought on board the helicopter. This is the information as of this hour. As new reports from our correspondents on the spot arrive, we will report them to you in Ostankino Novosti bulletins.
